1
00:00:16,460 --> 00:00:17,813
Rosanna!

2
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:23,090
I'm talking to you Rosanna
and I know you can hear me.

3
00:00:25,380 --> 00:00:28,770
Please see to it that Karl doesn't
spend entire Summer at the computer.

4
00:00:28,980 --> 00:00:32,859
And you too... don't read so much,
try to get outside also.

5
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:37,412
It's really beautiful over there.
You can ride the bikes anywhere.

6
00:00:39,340 --> 00:00:42,218
You don't want to talk to me?
- No.

7
00:00:44,420 --> 00:00:46,809
Rosanna, mom will need peace
after the surgery.

8
00:00:47,020 --> 00:00:49,409
You're a big girl already,
you should understand.

9
00:00:49,740 --> 00:00:51,537
What if I'll never see her again.

10
00:00:51,740 --> 00:00:53,935
Don't be foolish.

11
00:00:56,940 --> 00:00:59,408
The surgery could fail.

12
00:01:00,940 --> 00:01:04,410
Don't you ever say that.

13
00:01:05,220 --> 00:01:07,336
It can't fail.

14
00:01:18,380 --> 00:01:22,089
Friar Johannes and Brother Martinus
got real close to making gold.

15
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:24,613
Did you kill them?

16
00:01:24,820 --> 00:01:26,572
Recipe?!

17
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:29,857
Nobody must know about this.

18
00:01:30,540 --> 00:01:33,179
Nobody shall ever know.

19
00:01:37,380 --> 00:01:42,613
KID DETECTIVES AND
THE SCRET OF THE WHITE LADY

20
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:16,176
Markus! Are you deaf?

21
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:38,735
Markus!

22
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:42,218
I'm gonna be late for work,
you'll have to watch Emilia.

23
00:02:42,380 --> 00:02:43,654
I'm already big.

24
00:02:43,860 --> 00:02:45,612
Let me be the judge of that, okay.

25
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:47,731
You'll be home by 12.

26
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:50,291
I have to sell the books
of Mr. Krookus.

27
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:53,810
We're going to have guests,
have you already forgotten?

28
00:02:54,820 --> 00:02:57,812
Mom, why do we have to have strangers
here for the whole Summer?

29
00:02:58,020 --> 00:02:59,931
Loviis was my best friend at school.

30
00:03:00,140 --> 00:03:02,176
She asked for my help,
I couldn't turn her down.

31
00:03:02,380 --> 00:03:03,859
They will not ruin your summer.

32
00:03:04,060 --> 00:03:05,652
Rosanna and Karl
are almost your age.

33
00:03:05,860 --> 00:03:07,418
You'll have fun together.

34
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:09,053
Hey, help me close this.

35
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:11,211
Sometimes I wonder how many kids
do I really have.

36
00:03:12,820 --> 00:03:14,048
Well, go on.

37
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:17,457
And don't forget.
We've got tickets for tonight.

38
00:03:17,660 --> 00:03:18,456
Yeah-yeah.

39
00:03:27,580 --> 00:03:30,378
Did you do everything correctly,
Henricus?

40
00:03:30,580 --> 00:03:32,730
Yes, to create the homunculus,

41
00:03:33,460 --> 00:03:35,815
I took one portion of bones,

42
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:38,969
after that

43
00:03:39,940 --> 00:03:41,692
a little bit of semen

44
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:46,098
a bit skin and hair.

45
00:03:46,820 --> 00:03:50,893
From every animal homunculus
has to look like.

46
00:03:51,620 --> 00:03:56,614
Then I placed it all
in one container.

47
00:03:57,540 --> 00:04:01,658
Covered everything
with horse manure

48
00:04:02,660 --> 00:04:05,458
and left it for 40 days and 40 nights

49
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:07,697
untouched.

50
00:04:07,940 --> 00:04:11,057
Now 40 days have passed
and the fetus of the homunculus

51
00:04:11,260 --> 00:04:13,376
should be ready. Let's see it.
- Yes.

52
00:04:19,940 --> 00:04:22,534
Instead of a little person
all I see

53
00:04:22,740 --> 00:04:24,492
is horse manure.

54
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:27,339
Master, I did everything correctly.

55
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:29,770
It's already seventh attempt
that you have failed.

56
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:32,215
Throw this crap over the wall.

57
00:04:33,580 --> 00:04:34,933
What are you staring at!

58
00:04:35,780 --> 00:04:37,372
Haven't you seen crap before?

59
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:39,335
Go to work!

60
00:04:42,980 --> 00:04:45,858
Buy a thriller "White Lady's
True Legend".

61
00:04:46,300 --> 00:04:49,576
Written by our town's honorary
citizen Feliks Truu.

62
00:04:49,820 --> 00:04:52,175
The bloodcurling tale
of the White Lady.

63
00:04:52,340 --> 00:04:56,413
Witches, executioners
and burning of the witches.

64
00:04:56,980 --> 00:04:58,732
Torture on the wheel.

65
00:04:59,060 --> 00:05:01,449
This is stupid, nobody's
gonna buy it anyway.

66
00:05:02,060 --> 00:05:03,459
Let's try for another 10 minutes.

67
00:05:03,860 --> 00:05:04,849
Okay.

68
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:08,253
Only 7 euros and 9...
- Sorry.

69
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:11,216
What are you selling here?
- A book.

70
00:05:11,780 --> 00:05:14,533
Feliks Truu's "True Story
of the White Lady".

71
00:05:18,580 --> 00:05:20,810
So the White Lady was actually
an alchemist.

72
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:22,658
Very interesting theory.

73
00:05:23,820 --> 00:05:26,618
Let's make a deal. If you promise
me, that it's a good read,

74
00:05:26,820 --> 00:05:28,048
then I'll buy it.

75
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:30,256
I promise
- Promise?
- Yes.

76
00:05:32,140 --> 00:05:33,334
Keep the change.

77
00:05:33,780 --> 00:05:35,532
Go buy an icecream or something.

78
00:05:36,820 --> 00:05:37,935
And who might you be?

79
00:05:38,260 --> 00:05:39,409
I'm Emilia.

80
00:05:39,620 --> 00:05:43,579
Can you tell me where is
the bishop's castle's museum?

81
00:05:43,900 --> 00:05:46,050
Yes, it's right there,
around the corner.

82
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:48,768
By the way, my mom works there.

83
00:05:50,020 --> 00:05:51,339
Excellent!

84
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:53,811
Maybe I'll meet your mom today.

85
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:03,536
During the entire morning
we've had only three guests.

86
00:06:04,420 --> 00:06:07,617
If it continues like this,
we'll have to start firing people.

87
00:06:07,860 --> 00:06:10,818
But White Lady's days are coming.

88
00:06:11,020 --> 00:06:13,818
Then there's always more people.
- That's only temporary.

89
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:16,491
We need advertising.

90
00:06:16,820 --> 00:06:18,299
More advertising...
- Sorry!

91
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:21,016
I couldn't help overhearing
your discussion.

92
00:06:21,220 --> 00:06:24,690
When it comes to advertising,
I might be able to help you.

93
00:06:25,020 --> 00:06:26,214
Who might you be?

94
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:27,815
Excuse me!

95
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:32,818
I am a photographer, Stig,
Stig Velson.

96
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:40,496
I am making a photo book of Haapsalu,
of the Bishop's Castle,

97
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,815
to be more exact.

98
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:43,736
Excuse us.

99
00:06:45,660 --> 00:06:48,379
Berit, starting today,

100
00:06:48,620 --> 00:06:52,454
you will be at this gentleman's
disposal 24/7.

101
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:54,856
This is exactly the advertising that we need.

102
00:07:14,820 --> 00:07:15,855
Help!

103
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:18,173
Help!

104
00:08:05,660 --> 00:08:06,570
Hello.
- Hello.

105
00:08:07,380 --> 00:08:10,531
Hello, Markus. Hello, Emilia.

106
00:08:11,660 --> 00:08:13,457
How did you do today?

107
00:08:13,740 --> 00:08:17,619
Mr. Krookus, in three days we have
sold only two books.

108
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:21,497
One was bought by me and the other
one by a gentleman.

109
00:08:21,740 --> 00:08:26,370
So sad that people don't care
about the true history of their town.

110
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:30,368
Split the money between you two.

111
00:08:31,460 --> 00:08:33,849
Thanks.
- You've worked so hard.

112
00:08:36,060 --> 00:08:39,655
Are you sure that everything happened
like it's written in this book?

113
00:08:40,060 --> 00:08:43,211
Feliks Truu, this book's author

114
00:08:43,420 --> 00:08:46,935
was internationally renowned
archaeologist.

115
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:52,251
He devoted his entire life
to exploring our Bishop's castle.

116
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:56,015
He stumbled upon the manuscript
of Bonifacius

117
00:08:56,660 --> 00:09:00,175
and the White Lady's true story
is based on that.

118
00:09:00,420 --> 00:09:02,888
And where is this manuscript now?

119
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:07,090
Unfortunately Feliks Truu died
so suddenly

120
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:10,298
that he couldn't tell anyone.

121
00:09:24,900 --> 00:09:27,095
You have to be the last as always.

122
00:09:28,020 --> 00:09:30,739
Hurry, Emilia, we had to be home
2 minutes ago.

123
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:32,214
Good bye.
- Good bye.

124
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:41,533
Rosanna, try to look more cheerful,
this is embarassing.

125
00:09:46,220 --> 00:09:49,769
Remember, we'll be doing nothing
with these kids.

126
00:09:49,980 --> 00:09:51,015
But why?

127
00:09:51,220 --> 00:09:54,769
Our behaviour has to be so sucky
that they'll have to send us home.

128
00:09:54,980 --> 00:09:56,936
Is this clear?
- Yes.

129
00:09:57,300 --> 00:09:59,416
Come on in, don't be shy.

130
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:01,093
You'll be living here.

131
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:04,338
I'll take this bed.
- Take it if you want.

132
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:08,369
Thank you, you've really
put in an effort here.

133
00:10:08,580 --> 00:10:11,538
Summer room, it needed to be
fixed up for some time already.

134
00:10:11,740 --> 00:10:16,018
Kids were helping fully when they heard
they'll get playmates for summer.

135
00:10:16,940 --> 00:10:20,853
I'll be going then, that way
I'll get back in time to visit Loviis.

136
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:27,491
Be good and listen to Berit.
- See you.

137
00:10:37,620 --> 00:10:41,056
Don't worry, Rosanna takes a little
warming up but I can handle her.

138
00:10:45,140 --> 00:10:47,779
Rosanna, do you want to
play badmington?

139
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:49,857
I don't want to play
any stupid ballgames.

140
00:10:50,060 --> 00:10:51,288
Leave me alone!

141
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:22,490
Brother Franciscus is already
a third alchemist

142
00:11:22,980 --> 00:11:25,414
that has died this month.

143
00:11:26,820 --> 00:11:29,288
I think he stumbled
and fell off the wall.

144
00:11:29,700 --> 00:11:32,817
But brother Martinus
who fell down the well?

145
00:11:33,540 --> 00:11:34,939
And brother Johannes

146
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:38,731
who died unfortunately
after the supper?

147
00:11:39,420 --> 00:11:42,810
Lord works in mysterious ways,
beyond reason for men.

148
00:11:44,580 --> 00:11:46,810
They all worked on
manufacturing gold.

149
00:11:47,020 --> 00:11:50,171
I'm afraid somebody wants to
hamper our efforts.

150
00:11:50,380 --> 00:11:51,415
But who, Your Holiness?

151
00:11:51,620 --> 00:11:55,329
I don't know yet but I swear,
I'll find out.

152
00:11:59,860 --> 00:12:03,899
Hire yourself more
promising apprentices.

153
00:12:06,980 --> 00:12:10,416
Gold has to be ready
by the end of this year.

154
00:12:13,860 --> 00:12:16,294
And do not forget Homunculus.

155
00:12:23,380 --> 00:12:24,529
Take it away.

156
00:12:27,740 --> 00:12:29,492
I've lost my appetite.

157
00:12:51,460 --> 00:12:54,179
Freeze! Hands on your head!
Face the wall!

158
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:56,894
What are you doing here?

159
00:12:57,100 --> 00:13:00,297
I wanted to turn off the alarm
but something went wrong.

160
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:03,776
I opened a dance studio here.
- You may lower your hands.

161
00:13:06,100 --> 00:13:08,250
May I see your documents?

162
00:13:12,220 --> 00:13:13,096
Here you go.

163
00:13:15,060 --> 00:13:16,379
Please, come on in!

164
00:13:16,580 --> 00:13:20,016
I have to thank you somehow
for saving me from trouble.

165
00:13:21,460 --> 00:13:22,529
Maybe a cup of coffee?

166
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:24,970
No, I have to go. Work matters.

167
00:13:25,420 --> 00:13:27,490
Maybe you would be interested
in dance lessons?

168
00:13:27,660 --> 00:13:29,298
For you I would give these for free.

169
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:32,253
Look, dancing and me,
these don't match.

170
00:13:32,460 --> 00:13:34,496
Don't be so modest.

171
00:13:35,420 --> 00:13:36,694
Take this at least.

172
00:13:37,140 --> 00:13:37,970
Thank you!

173
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:39,699
See you later, Tonis Piir.

174
00:13:39,900 --> 00:13:42,414
See you later, Karin Viisle.

175
00:13:57,420 --> 00:13:59,217
Don't you ever regret it?

176
00:13:59,780 --> 00:14:01,054
Regret what?

177
00:14:02,740 --> 00:14:05,379
Marrying a man who can't dance,

178
00:14:05,700 --> 00:14:07,372
sent to work to in the province?

179
00:14:08,260 --> 00:14:09,852
Oh, come on!

180
00:14:26,660 --> 00:14:29,015
Good boys!

181
00:14:29,780 --> 00:14:32,010
Everyone within five seconds.

182
00:14:45,620 --> 00:14:47,338
And you, you lazy bum,

183
00:14:47,980 --> 00:14:49,732
what are you stalling?

184
00:14:54,020 --> 00:14:55,578
One more.

185
00:14:58,420 --> 00:15:00,729
I'm coming, coming.

186
00:15:03,740 --> 00:15:05,537
Hello.
- Hello...

187
00:15:15,420 --> 00:15:17,331
Yes. Piir here.

188
00:15:19,420 --> 00:15:21,092
To Krookus' house?

189
00:15:21,740 --> 00:15:24,334
Okay, I'll stop by the station.
Be right there.

190
00:15:25,140 --> 00:15:27,973
What happened? 
- Break in at Krookus'store.

191
00:15:29,700 --> 00:15:30,894
I'll take you home.

192
00:15:31,220 --> 00:15:33,814
No. I want to listen
to the music.

193
00:15:46,060 --> 00:15:47,937
Would you care to dance?

194
00:15:48,660 --> 00:15:50,093
I'd love to.

195
00:15:51,660 --> 00:15:54,936
My dearest possessions, gone.
- Please remove your hand.

196
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:58,412
The robbers had to know
precisely what to take?

197
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:00,816
They didn't know anything.

198
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:04,730
There are clocks many times
more valuable

199
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:08,255
You said it yourself,
your dearest clocks.

200
00:16:08,460 --> 00:16:10,576
I didn't mean it like this.
The thing is

201
00:16:10,980 --> 00:16:13,699
Those clocks belonged
to our town's honorary citizen

202
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:14,856
Mister...

203
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:16,368
Don't touch! 
- Sorry!

204
00:16:16,580 --> 00:16:17,899
...Feliks Truu.

205
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:21,934
After his death I bought those
clocks from his daughter.

206
00:16:22,540 --> 00:16:24,417
These have very high... 
- Please.

207
00:16:25,060 --> 00:16:27,210
...cultural value. 
- I see.

208
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:29,299
One was up there.

209
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:31,258
And another one was here

210
00:16:34,580 --> 00:16:35,774
Please, come and sit here.

211
00:16:35,980 --> 00:16:38,050
Here were two really valuable clocks.

212
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:40,491
Here and here. 
- Please, just sit.

213
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:41,530
Yes, thank you.

214
00:16:41,740 --> 00:16:43,810
Let me take the photos, do my job.

215
00:16:45,860 --> 00:16:47,179
Down here.

216
00:16:48,420 --> 00:16:50,251
God, what a great misfortune!

217
00:17:55,820 --> 00:17:57,651
Oh, hi. 
- Hello-hello.

218
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:00,860
May I introduce my husband Tonis.

219
00:18:01,260 --> 00:18:04,411
Stig Velson, photographer,
I told you about him.

220
00:18:04,780 --> 00:18:05,735
Hello.

221
00:18:06,380 --> 00:18:07,176
Hello.

222
00:18:07,340 --> 00:18:10,093
It was lovely, Berit, but
unfortunately I have to go now.

223
00:18:10,620 --> 00:18:12,178
Good evening. 
- Good evening.

224
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:16,936
That photographer seemed
like a pretty skilled dancer.

225
00:18:17,140 --> 00:18:18,539
You noticed?

226
00:18:19,020 --> 00:18:20,897
It was impossible not to.

227
00:18:23,100 --> 00:18:24,169
Shall we go?

228
00:18:33,660 --> 00:18:35,730
Kids, meal is ready!

229
00:18:37,620 --> 00:18:38,609
Where are you going?

230
00:18:38,860 --> 00:18:39,736
To eat.

231
00:18:40,020 --> 00:18:40,850
You're not going anywhere.

232
00:18:41,220 --> 00:18:44,018
We'll declare a hunger strike
until they send us home.

233
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:47,019
You can starve if you want
but I'm hungry.

234
00:18:47,300 --> 00:18:49,018
Then you're a traitor. Nerd.

235
00:18:49,820 --> 00:18:52,778
I'm not a traitor and I'm no nerd.
- Are too.

236
00:18:53,020 --> 00:18:54,772
And a suck-up. 
- Do you know...

237
00:18:55,860 --> 00:18:57,896
We should be with mom right now.
Get it?

238
00:18:58,100 --> 00:19:01,058
I think we should do
as mom and dad told us.

239
00:19:04,220 --> 00:19:05,653
Good morning. 
- Hi.

240
00:19:07,260 --> 00:19:08,249
Where's Rosanna?

241
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:10,179
She didn't want to eat.

242
00:19:17,340 --> 00:19:18,250
Rosanna!

243
00:19:19,900 --> 00:19:22,892
I'm not going to pretend like
nothing bad hasn't happened.

244
00:19:23,100 --> 00:19:25,739
Your mom is sick, about to have
a difficult surgery.

245
00:19:25,940 --> 00:19:29,216
I'm sure there will come a time
when you have to support her.

246
00:19:29,420 --> 00:19:31,695
Therefore there's no point
to starve yourself to death.

247
00:19:32,420 --> 00:19:34,172
I'll never see mom again.

248
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:36,535
Mom promised you that
you'll meet again.

249
00:19:37,140 --> 00:19:37,731
Promised, promised.

250
00:19:37,940 --> 00:19:40,170
Only to get us away from there.

251
00:19:40,780 --> 00:19:42,372
As much as I know Loviis,

252
00:19:42,580 --> 00:19:45,890
She never breaks her promises
and we studied together for 12 years.

253
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:48,930
Rosanna.

254
00:19:51,980 --> 00:19:55,177
Your mom would never lie to you
in such important matters.

255
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:58,053
Come, eat something.

256
00:19:58,660 --> 00:20:00,651
Later you can go cycling.

257
00:20:00,860 --> 00:20:04,330
Markus knows all sorts of cool places,
ruins and secret passageways.

258
00:20:04,540 --> 00:20:05,529
Come!

259
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:11,252
And you shall see green flame

260
00:20:11,540 --> 00:20:13,053
that comes from phosphorus.

261
00:20:19,900 --> 00:20:22,368
What evil spirit has sent you
to this place?

262
00:20:22,580 --> 00:20:24,775
I came because you called,
my name is Johan.

263
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:26,778
I heard you're looking
for an apprentice.

264
00:20:26,980 --> 00:20:30,529
I could use a good apprentice,
but not one so eager

265
00:20:30,780 --> 00:20:32,930
who would blow up my workshop.

266
00:20:33,820 --> 00:20:35,173
What are you giggling about?

267
00:20:35,980 --> 00:20:37,254
You finish the homunculus.

268
00:20:38,420 --> 00:20:40,092
Where are you from?
- From the village.

269
00:20:40,300 --> 00:20:41,972
I live with my mom.

270
00:20:42,380 --> 00:20:45,338
My father was a doctor and an alchemist.
I learned these arts from him.

271
00:20:46,260 --> 00:20:47,375
All right.

272
00:20:48,780 --> 00:20:50,338
You can stay, for now.

273
00:20:58,460 --> 00:21:01,054
Careful, I just got my hair done.

274
00:21:01,300 --> 00:21:03,939
Tomorrow there's a jazz night at the
club. I rescheduled my shift.

275
00:21:04,140 --> 00:21:05,653
I bought us two tickets.

276
00:21:06,860 --> 00:21:09,579
Tonis, that is so sweet.

277
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:12,211
But tomorrow I can't.

278
00:21:12,700 --> 00:21:13,815
What are you doing tomorrow?

279
00:21:14,020 --> 00:21:16,488
I'm going to Noarootsi, to photograph
the sunset with Stig.

280
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:18,895
We have agreed with local fishermen.

281
00:21:19,660 --> 00:21:23,539
Some other time. 
- Don't be upset! That was really sweet.

282
00:21:25,100 --> 00:21:26,215
Let's go!

283
00:21:50,260 --> 00:21:51,295
Hello. 
- Hello.

284
00:21:51,820 --> 00:21:52,889
I'm on a break.

285
00:21:53,100 --> 00:21:56,172
Thought I'd come by.
Check your security.

286
00:21:57,300 --> 00:22:00,019
Great that you're concerned
for my security.

287
00:22:00,660 --> 00:22:03,891
Come on in, let's see if
you're really that talentless.

288
00:22:04,100 --> 00:22:04,896
I don't know.

289
00:22:07,380 --> 00:22:09,177
I have no sense of rhythm.

290
00:22:09,340 --> 00:22:11,092
Nobody is so unmusical

291
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:12,733
that they couldn't be
taught to dance.

292
00:22:12,940 --> 00:22:14,896
You think so? 
- Sure. Let's go.

293
00:22:16,620 --> 00:22:17,814
Come in!

294
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:20,649
Hello. 
- Hello.

295
00:22:21,420 --> 00:22:22,011
Hi.

296
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:26,929
They are Rosanna and Karl.
They spend summer with us.

297
00:22:27,740 --> 00:22:29,412
Hello, Karl. 
- Hello.

298
00:22:29,780 --> 00:22:30,690
Hello, Rosanna.

299
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:34,298
Mr. Krookus, I heard that
you were robbed last night.

300
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:35,376
Yes I was.

301
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:38,498
Number of costly clocks they took,
those scoundrels.

302
00:22:38,820 --> 00:22:41,892
Could we look for those clock-robbers?

303
00:22:42,660 --> 00:22:44,616
Your dad is already handling this.

304
00:22:44,820 --> 00:22:47,618
He came by last night,
photographed everything.

305
00:22:47,860 --> 00:22:49,612
Dad is so busy all the time.

306
00:22:49,940 --> 00:22:51,737
We have much more time.

307
00:22:51,940 --> 00:22:55,216
And besides, we would also
like to solve cases.

308
00:22:55,580 --> 00:22:58,219
Yearning for a true case.

309
00:23:00,060 --> 00:23:02,938
So be it, young detectives.

310
00:23:03,420 --> 00:23:04,773
I'm hiring you.

311
00:23:05,460 --> 00:23:07,849
And if you catch those robbers

312
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:11,576
then I guarantee you free icecream
for the whole summer.

313
00:23:11,780 --> 00:23:14,817
Deal! 
- Emilia and Karl,
you will check that corner.

314
00:23:14,980 --> 00:23:16,538
Rosanna, you'll check
from over there.

315
00:23:16,820 --> 00:23:19,539
I'm in charge of the whole operation.
- Maybe vice versa?

316
00:23:19,740 --> 00:23:20,968
You'll check that corner over there.

317
00:23:21,220 --> 00:23:24,212
And I'm in charge of the operation.
- OK, let's investigate together.

318
00:23:29,460 --> 00:23:32,213
I found something.
- Wait, don't touch.

319
00:23:39,860 --> 00:23:42,818
Mister Krookus, is this yours?

320
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:45,768
No, it's certainly not mine.

321
00:23:46,100 --> 00:23:48,375
The bad guys probably dropped this.

322
00:23:49,140 --> 00:23:50,812
Here are fingerprints.

323
00:23:51,220 --> 00:23:54,178
Look what smart kids you are

324
00:23:59,900 --> 00:24:02,016
I'll get the fingerprints.

325
00:24:10,660 --> 00:24:13,299
Where did you learn this?
- Dad taught me.

326
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:17,336
We have two fingerprints.

327
00:24:17,980 --> 00:24:20,369
How do you know whom
these belong to?

328
00:24:20,620 --> 00:24:23,771
That we may find out through
police databank.

329
00:24:25,620 --> 00:24:27,770
Only we have to get
to dad's office somehow.

330
00:24:28,020 --> 00:24:30,818
Maybe you'll ask dad
to let you take a look?

331
00:24:31,020 --> 00:24:31,816
Are you kidding?

332
00:24:32,020 --> 00:24:34,693
He'll have a seizure if I step
near his work computer.

333
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:37,095
I've crashed it numerous times.

334
00:24:37,460 --> 00:24:38,449
But let's do it like this!

335
00:24:40,380 --> 00:24:42,575
Nobody's coming. Now!

336
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:51,728
Yes.

337
00:24:53,500 --> 00:24:55,536
Stay there. I'll come right away.

338
00:24:55,900 --> 00:24:57,777
Dammit!

339
00:25:20,220 --> 00:25:21,892
There's one match.

340
00:25:22,100 --> 00:25:24,091
Your dad is coming. Hurry!

341
00:25:27,900 --> 00:25:29,652
Where on earth were you?

342
00:25:29,860 --> 00:25:31,088
We were riding our bikes.

343
00:25:31,340 --> 00:25:32,819
What happened? 
- What happened?!

344
00:25:33,220 --> 00:25:35,688
You should have looked
after the small ones.

345
00:25:35,900 --> 00:25:38,209
Emilia and Karl wandered around
and Karl fell in the water.

346
00:25:38,420 --> 00:25:40,888
If he catches a cold I have
no idea what to tell Loviis.

347
00:25:41,100 --> 00:25:42,692
My legs are melting.

348
00:25:42,900 --> 00:25:45,016
Hang on, dear. You'll get
hot tea in a minute.

349
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:46,415
With raspberries and honey.

350
00:25:46,620 --> 00:25:48,975
Did you find the owner
of the fingerprints?

351
00:25:49,220 --> 00:25:51,370
Yes, we did. Your self-sacrifice
was worth it.

352
00:25:51,580 --> 00:25:54,856
These belong to Roobert Uurike,
address Sambla 41.

353
00:25:55,300 --> 00:25:57,575
After it gets dark, me and Markus will go there

354
00:25:57,780 --> 00:25:58,815
Get lost!

355
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:08,334
So...

356
00:26:10,700 --> 00:26:11,530
What is it?

357
00:26:11,740 --> 00:26:13,014
Honorable teacher.

358
00:26:13,260 --> 00:26:17,572
I believe I have found a way
to hasten healing of the wounds.

359
00:26:17,940 --> 00:26:18,770
Oh?

360
00:26:29,780 --> 00:26:31,975
This is a true miracle.

361
00:26:32,220 --> 00:26:35,849
I would like to get so far that my
elixir would cure all illnesses.

362
00:26:36,620 --> 00:26:39,692
Pure hokum. There is no cure
for the plague.

363
00:26:39,900 --> 00:26:42,175
There is no cure for
your aching head.

364
00:26:43,900 --> 00:26:45,777
Bishop demands gold.

365
00:26:46,140 --> 00:26:48,973
Therefore I cannot allow you
to continue with the cure.

366
00:26:50,700 --> 00:26:55,569
Look for the Sorcerer's Stone.
That will help us turn metal into gold.

367
00:26:59,420 --> 00:27:02,412
Brother Johan. Don't worry,
I'll help you.

368
00:27:02,700 --> 00:27:05,294
We will work on your elixir
at nights.

369
00:27:27,300 --> 00:27:28,858
Where do you think you're going?

370
00:27:29,060 --> 00:27:30,778
We want to come with you.

371
00:27:30,980 --> 00:27:32,652
I told you, you're too small.

372
00:27:32,860 --> 00:27:35,420
If you don't take us with you,
I'll scream.

373
00:27:35,580 --> 00:27:39,493
Okay, you can come,
but no whining.

374
00:27:52,660 --> 00:27:55,697
That photographer has rented
an apartment here.

375
00:28:11,900 --> 00:28:15,256
Me and Rosanna will go first,
then you'll follow.

376
00:28:20,860 --> 00:28:23,772
Let me tell you, Aivar.

377
00:28:25,260 --> 00:28:27,979
We have to get a new dog.

378
00:28:28,220 --> 00:28:31,974
I hate it when I don't know if someone's
sneaking around my house or not.

379
00:28:32,940 --> 00:28:35,408
First time to have a dog's wake.

380
00:28:35,940 --> 00:28:37,817
Bottoms up.

381
00:28:38,740 --> 00:28:41,812
Wait! That sounded so familiar.

382
00:28:42,460 --> 00:28:44,257
Exactly like the clock Mr. Krookus had.

383
00:28:44,460 --> 00:28:46,974
Exactly. It came from there.

384
00:28:55,540 --> 00:28:57,815
They are the ones who robbed
the clock of Mr. Krookus.

385
00:28:59,460 --> 00:29:01,496
You're a really smart kid.

386
00:29:10,500 --> 00:29:13,378
Tonis! 
- Yes?
- The kids are gone.

387
00:29:15,900 --> 00:29:18,494
As long as they didn't go swimming
on their own.

388
00:29:18,700 --> 00:29:20,895
We'll find them, don't worry.

389
00:29:23,860 --> 00:29:25,259
There's an alarm all over the county.

390
00:29:25,460 --> 00:29:27,655
Four kids on bikes cannot be
unseen for too long.

391
00:29:27,860 --> 00:29:31,773
We'll look by the lighthouse as well.
- Okay.

392
00:30:01,020 --> 00:30:04,330
Good day, officer Piir.
May I see your licence please.

393
00:30:12,740 --> 00:30:15,300
You didn't see four kids on bicycles?

394
00:30:15,500 --> 00:30:19,209
No sir, we didn't see
no kids anywhere, officer.

395
00:30:21,580 --> 00:30:23,411
Please open the backdoor.

396
00:30:24,620 --> 00:30:26,736
Sure, no problem.

397
00:30:33,220 --> 00:30:34,892
We're transporting old furniture.

398
00:30:42,220 --> 00:30:44,211
You can close this.

399
00:30:46,500 --> 00:30:49,253
Drive safe. 
- Thanks! All the best to you as well.

400
00:31:31,020 --> 00:31:32,612
Out of the car!

401
00:31:34,340 --> 00:31:36,376
Face down, on the ground,
hands on your back.

402
00:31:36,860 --> 00:31:37,576
Face down, face down.

403
00:31:39,140 --> 00:31:40,255
Hands on your back!

404
00:31:45,540 --> 00:31:47,337
Did you wind the clocks?

405
00:31:47,740 --> 00:31:48,490
Well, yeah.

406
00:31:48,820 --> 00:31:51,573
The sound is so beautiful.

407
00:31:52,060 --> 00:31:52,970
Idiot.

408
00:32:00,100 --> 00:32:02,250
If only you knew what
I had to live through.

409
00:32:02,460 --> 00:32:04,690
I have a handful of grey hair.

410
00:32:04,900 --> 00:32:06,811
But Mom, nothing happened to us.

411
00:32:07,060 --> 00:32:08,732
But could have happened.

412
00:32:08,940 --> 00:32:10,851
Besided, you're dying your hair anyway.

413
00:32:12,100 --> 00:32:13,010
Thanks!

414
00:32:15,420 --> 00:32:19,095
The only good thing here is
that kids caught the clock robbers.

415
00:32:29,460 --> 00:32:31,212
A year's worth of work,
brother Johan,

416
00:32:31,540 --> 00:32:34,532
But now it seems that the elixir
might be finally ready.

417
00:32:36,140 --> 00:32:38,495
I hope it will be useful for people.

418
00:32:38,700 --> 00:32:40,292
Whom shall we try it on first?

419
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:42,491
I want to test this on myself.

420
00:32:42,700 --> 00:32:46,056
I'm a little ill. If I get better
then the cure has power.

421
00:32:48,260 --> 00:32:50,296
All right. But please be careful!

422
00:32:50,500 --> 00:32:52,730
We don't know about the side effects.

423
00:33:00,140 --> 00:33:01,539
I can't breathe!

424
00:33:03,540 --> 00:33:04,814
Johan!

425
00:33:16,140 --> 00:33:18,210
Are you going to turn me in?

426
00:33:24,620 --> 00:33:25,894
Don't be afraid!

427
00:33:29,820 --> 00:33:32,414
So, you two, together again.

428
00:33:33,340 --> 00:33:34,455
Jacob!

429
00:33:35,460 --> 00:33:37,291
No more coughing.

430
00:33:40,300 --> 00:33:42,370
Mom, how are you doing?

431
00:33:43,940 --> 00:33:47,569
Fine. Dad visits me every day.

432
00:33:47,940 --> 00:33:50,977
I'm, getting preparatory treatment
and I feel quite good.

433
00:33:51,220 --> 00:33:52,414
When is the surgery?

434
00:33:52,660 --> 00:33:53,934
Next week.

435
00:33:54,140 --> 00:33:55,573
When are you getting out?

436
00:33:55,780 --> 00:33:59,659
It'll be couple of more weeks after the
surgery and then we'll see each other.

437
00:34:01,260 --> 00:34:02,852
I have to go now.

438
00:34:03,140 --> 00:34:05,529
Time for my procedures,
nurse came.

439
00:34:05,820 --> 00:34:07,299
Hugs and kisses.

440
00:34:07,740 --> 00:34:08,775
See you!

441
00:34:19,260 --> 00:34:20,739
Teacher. 
- Yes, what is it?

442
00:34:21,300 --> 00:34:23,336
Here's a cure that can help
lots of people.

443
00:34:23,540 --> 00:34:25,895
We prepared this with brother
Jacob at nights

444
00:34:26,220 --> 00:34:28,415
I told you not to work
on the cure.

445
00:34:28,580 --> 00:34:30,650
But ill people need to be cured,
there's a plague in town.

446
00:34:30,860 --> 00:34:32,771
Teacher, we're asking
for your permission

447
00:34:32,980 --> 00:34:35,938
To try this on the patients
of the hospital.

448
00:34:36,140 --> 00:34:38,779
Because the cure may still have
dangerous side effects.

449
00:34:38,980 --> 00:34:40,777
This is no cure.

450
00:34:40,980 --> 00:34:43,972
That's poison, stirred by Devil's tail.

451
00:34:45,820 --> 00:34:47,378
I cannot allow this.

452
00:34:47,580 --> 00:34:49,935
We have to search for the
Sorcerer's Stone and make gold.

453
00:34:50,540 --> 00:34:52,019
Bishop's patience is wearing thin.

454
00:34:53,220 --> 00:34:55,734
Tests with the cure shall be postponed.

455
00:34:56,420 --> 00:34:57,933
And remember this,

456
00:34:58,220 --> 00:35:00,654
Alchemy is knowledge

457
00:35:00,860 --> 00:35:04,569
about creation of the form
and its disappearance.

458
00:35:05,620 --> 00:35:07,975
How is homunculus coming along?

459
00:35:12,740 --> 00:35:13,934
Please.

460
00:35:22,340 --> 00:35:24,376
Karl, 5 minutes is up,
it's my turn.

461
00:35:24,580 --> 00:35:26,298
It's not yet 5 minutes.

462
00:35:26,540 --> 00:35:28,417
Yes it is, give up the dog.

463
00:35:28,620 --> 00:35:29,609
Take it!

464
00:35:31,740 --> 00:35:33,458
That photographer again.

465
00:35:34,940 --> 00:35:36,373
Why don't you like him?

466
00:35:36,580 --> 00:35:38,935
I don't and that's it. Stuffing
his nose everywhere.

467
00:35:39,260 --> 00:35:41,171
Siding up to Mom as well.

468
00:35:41,380 --> 00:35:42,938
I think he's pretty cool.

469
00:35:49,100 --> 00:35:51,216
Come! 
- What place is this?

470
00:35:51,500 --> 00:35:53,456
It used to be monastery's library.

471
00:35:53,660 --> 00:35:56,174
Now it's been empty for years.

472
00:35:57,620 --> 00:35:58,814
Look!

473
00:36:02,420 --> 00:36:04,729
I've collecting these things here,
one by one

474
00:36:04,980 --> 00:36:07,733
We'll start making your
healing elixir here.

475
00:36:10,020 --> 00:36:11,692
My father used to deal with alchemy.

476
00:36:12,220 --> 00:36:14,415
After he died from the plague
I promised myself

477
00:36:14,620 --> 00:36:17,180
that I will make an elixir
that would cure all illnesses.

478
00:36:19,340 --> 00:36:21,774
When I saw you for the first time,

479
00:36:22,980 --> 00:36:24,493
then I felt as if

480
00:36:24,780 --> 00:36:27,248
I'd never seen a face more beautiful.

481
00:36:39,500 --> 00:36:41,934
Higher. From the pose.

482
00:36:42,260 --> 00:36:45,536
Grab me from here. Don't
be afraid, I won't bite. Now I feel.

483
00:36:46,220 --> 00:36:47,619
From here it's lifted.

484
00:36:48,020 --> 00:36:51,695
Fingers round my hand, strong,
knees slightly bent.

485
00:37:03,900 --> 00:37:04,730
Dad!?

486
00:37:04,940 --> 00:37:06,339
What's he doing here?

487
00:37:06,620 --> 00:37:08,975
If my eyes are correct
then he's learning to tango.

488
00:37:09,340 --> 00:37:11,649
But he hates dancing.

489
00:37:19,380 --> 00:37:21,496
You got caught!

490
00:37:22,980 --> 00:37:25,414
Dad, you're taking dance lessons!
- No.

491
00:37:26,300 --> 00:37:28,336
Yes. But don't mention this to mom.

492
00:37:28,540 --> 00:37:30,337
Do you want to surprise her?

493
00:37:30,580 --> 00:37:33,538
Surprise is the right word.
Do we have a deal?

494
00:37:51,140 --> 00:37:52,493
Heureka!

495
00:37:56,340 --> 00:37:57,773
You are really at it.

496
00:37:57,980 --> 00:38:00,050
It's you, Brother. Yes.

497
00:38:01,140 --> 00:38:02,812
I found the solution

498
00:38:03,060 --> 00:38:07,258
how to get even purer gold,
wrote down the formulas.

499
00:38:08,740 --> 00:38:10,219
Excellent.

500
00:38:37,220 --> 00:38:38,539
Are you going somewhere?

501
00:38:38,740 --> 00:38:40,856
Yes, work-related.

502
00:38:41,460 --> 00:38:42,859
Now?

503
00:38:43,060 --> 00:38:45,255
I forgot to tell you.

504
00:38:45,620 --> 00:38:48,054
Can you imagine what idea Stig had?

505
00:38:48,380 --> 00:38:52,692
He wants to go to the castle at night,
to shoot it in moonlight.

506
00:38:54,780 --> 00:38:56,850
And you're the one
who has to go with him?

507
00:38:57,100 --> 00:39:00,490
Yes. Director's orders, to be
at his disposal around the clock.

508
00:39:00,740 --> 00:39:02,378
He has to finish the book.

509
00:39:02,620 --> 00:39:04,292
What choice do I have?

510
00:39:05,100 --> 00:39:07,170
I've become downright
irreplacable for him

511
00:39:07,340 --> 00:39:10,537
Feels like this Stig can't even
go to the bathroom without you.

512
00:39:11,220 --> 00:39:13,939
Okay then, there he is.

513
00:39:15,260 --> 00:39:18,491
I hope officer Fear isn't jealous.

514
00:39:20,300 --> 00:39:21,335
No.

515
00:39:21,940 --> 00:39:24,534
No reason to be. I'll be back
in couple of hours.

516
00:39:24,740 --> 00:39:26,935
Ciao, don't be so grumpy.

517
00:39:39,500 --> 00:39:43,379
You're still talking about coincidence,
dear Bonifacius.

518
00:39:43,620 --> 00:39:47,010
Holy Father, this is the handywork
of Devil himself

