00:44:04,500 --> 00:44:05,819
These he would not believe.

578
00:44:06,020 --> 00:44:10,218
I'll add an old lady's picture
and make it transparent.

579
00:44:10,740 --> 00:44:12,651
Okay. I'll look around.

580
00:44:18,940 --> 00:44:20,259
What?

581
00:44:20,580 --> 00:44:22,730
Stig has a gun. 
- Show me

582
00:44:23,500 --> 00:44:24,728
Put it back.

583
00:44:30,340 --> 00:44:32,376
Look, if Stig sees this,

584
00:44:32,580 --> 00:44:34,775
he'll be gone from this town
in a few hours.

585
00:44:35,140 --> 00:44:36,175
Hang on.

586
00:44:37,100 --> 00:44:40,456
Look. Here's a folder on Mr. Krookus.
Open it.

587
00:44:44,380 --> 00:44:46,735
He has been following Mr. Krookus.

588
00:44:47,220 --> 00:44:49,609
Karl, make a copy of this folder.

589
00:44:50,100 --> 00:44:50,816
Yes.

590
00:44:53,780 --> 00:44:54,895
We can go.

591
00:45:00,140 --> 00:45:02,017
I don't want to be here.

592
00:45:02,300 --> 00:45:04,530
Let me go.

593
00:45:05,540 --> 00:45:07,053
Henricus

594
00:45:07,540 --> 00:45:10,657
you have committed heinous murders.

595
00:45:11,140 --> 00:45:12,619
Confess everything.

596
00:45:13,980 --> 00:45:17,734
I have nothing to confess, Holy Father.

597
00:45:18,260 --> 00:45:21,218
I don't know why I am here.

598
00:45:21,500 --> 00:45:25,459
Tell us where did you hide the recipe
for making gold.

599
00:45:26,140 --> 00:45:31,658
I know nothing, let me go.

600
00:45:34,300 --> 00:45:37,815
Executioner, you're not doing
a proper job.

601
00:45:44,780 --> 00:45:46,293
I confess.

602
00:45:46,540 --> 00:45:49,054
I killed them all.

603
00:45:49,380 --> 00:45:50,210
Me.

604
00:45:50,700 --> 00:45:52,372
Why did you do it, brother?

605
00:45:52,700 --> 00:45:54,850
Greed.

606
00:45:56,380 --> 00:45:59,338
I... I wanted that...

607
00:45:59,940 --> 00:46:04,491
only I would have instructions
for making gold.

608
00:46:06,500 --> 00:46:11,620
That only I would know the
secret of the Sorcerer's Stone.

609
00:46:12,260 --> 00:46:16,936
Tell us, where did you hide
the formula!

610
00:46:19,900 --> 00:46:21,618
It's in my chamber.

611
00:46:23,860 --> 00:46:26,977
There's a loose stone in the wall.

612
00:46:29,500 --> 00:46:31,058
Behind it.

613
00:46:39,300 --> 00:46:42,019
Mr. Krookus, we found
something really important.

614
00:46:42,940 --> 00:46:46,774
Pictures of your clocks and you,
in a person's computer.

615
00:46:46,980 --> 00:46:47,890
In addition to that,

616
00:46:48,100 --> 00:46:50,819
He had a copy of a letter
by professor Feliks Truu.

617
00:46:51,860 --> 00:46:54,055
The only thing familiar was
the name of Feliks Truu.

618
00:46:54,300 --> 00:46:57,656
One time I bought some clocks
from his daughter.

619
00:46:58,540 --> 00:47:00,178
Stamp albums, books

620
00:47:00,420 --> 00:47:04,732
And his manuscript to the
White Lady's true story.

621
00:47:04,980 --> 00:47:07,494
We printed out Feliks Truu's letter.

622
00:47:14,980 --> 00:47:16,379
"My dear daughter,

623
00:47:16,780 --> 00:47:18,771
if you're reading this, it means

624
00:47:18,980 --> 00:47:23,292
You have discovered it inside
"Guide to photography's" back cover.

625
00:47:24,300 --> 00:47:27,497
I hope you noticed our
secret marking on the back.

626
00:47:28,300 --> 00:47:31,849
I want to tell you that inside
one of the clocks I hid

627
00:47:32,300 --> 00:47:34,655
a very valuable treasure.

628
00:47:35,020 --> 00:47:39,536
Find it and decide for yourself
what to do with it."

629
00:47:43,580 --> 00:47:46,378
I believe we are really close
to creating the elixir.

630
00:47:46,580 --> 00:47:48,571
Did you add enough garlic?

631
00:47:48,780 --> 00:47:50,418
I believe so.

632
00:47:51,340 --> 00:47:52,489
What is it?

633
00:47:52,780 --> 00:47:54,657
It cannot start now.

634
00:47:56,620 --> 00:47:58,099
Can it wait?

635
00:47:59,660 --> 00:48:01,730
It's time, you have to help me.

636
00:48:03,300 --> 00:48:04,858
I'll teach you.

637
00:48:05,060 --> 00:48:09,372
I need clean clothes
and warm water.

638
00:48:13,820 --> 00:48:14,696
Go on!

639
00:48:15,940 --> 00:48:20,218
How is the gold-making
coming along?

640
00:48:21,660 --> 00:48:23,969
What's the matter with Brother Johan?

641
00:48:24,300 --> 00:48:27,098
Teacher, we have sinned.

642
00:48:27,940 --> 00:48:29,419
What sin?

643
00:48:30,300 --> 00:48:32,450
My real name is Johanna.

644
00:48:32,700 --> 00:48:36,329
I hid that I'm a girl, or you wouldn't have
accepted me as an apprentice.

645
00:48:38,260 --> 00:48:40,171
What are you looking at, you sinner!

646
00:48:40,340 --> 00:48:42,649
Go bring a strong stick
and warm water.

647
00:48:42,860 --> 00:48:45,579
And see that no-one finds out.

648
00:49:18,700 --> 00:49:21,658
Feliks Truu wrote this letter
to his daughter

649
00:49:22,220 --> 00:49:24,051
and hid it inside a book.

650
00:49:25,140 --> 00:49:26,892
Wait, how did you get this?

651
00:49:27,100 --> 00:49:31,651
We snuck into the house of Stig,
a photographer

652
00:49:32,140 --> 00:49:33,971
and I hacked his computer

653
00:49:34,220 --> 00:49:39,340
And Markus found a gun
belonging to that photographer.

654
00:49:42,460 --> 00:49:42,972
Hello.

655
00:49:43,220 --> 00:49:46,610
I have to show you something.
Can I come in? 
- Hello.

656
00:49:48,220 --> 00:49:49,733
Hello. 
- Hi there.

657
00:49:51,300 --> 00:49:53,609
I'm sorry, I shouldn't have barged
in early in the morning,

658
00:49:53,820 --> 00:49:55,253
but it is really important.

659
00:49:55,460 --> 00:49:59,817
I managed to catch White Lady
on a photo last night.

660
00:50:01,420 --> 00:50:05,379
What are you talking about.
We never saw the White Lady.

661
00:50:06,540 --> 00:50:08,496
But take a look at this photo.

662
00:50:09,660 --> 00:50:11,093
I took this last night.

663
00:50:11,740 --> 00:50:14,777
It is said that it is impossible
to see the ghosts in plain sight.

664
00:50:19,340 --> 00:50:23,413
This must be the young girl
buried in the christening chapel.

665
00:50:24,140 --> 00:50:25,255
That's the White Lady.

666
00:50:25,460 --> 00:50:28,179
You're not taking this seriously?
These are just myths.

667
00:50:29,100 --> 00:50:32,058
But this young woman's image
couldn't just, out of the blue

668
00:50:32,260 --> 00:50:35,297
appear on the photograph.

669
00:50:36,780 --> 00:50:40,455
That is strange. Maybe it's just
light effec t.

670
00:50:41,940 --> 00:50:45,376
Doesn't look like it. Look, see.

671
00:50:46,220 --> 00:50:47,812
I'm writing an article about this.

672
00:50:48,540 --> 00:50:51,373
By God, White Lady finally
caught on a photograph.

673
00:50:53,700 --> 00:50:57,613
No kids? Thought I'd show them
also the White Lady.

674
00:50:57,820 --> 00:51:00,175
They went to see Mr. Krookus
about an hour ago.

675
00:51:00,620 --> 00:51:01,416
There!

676
00:51:02,300 --> 00:51:03,813
Working on some cases again?

677
00:51:04,020 --> 00:51:07,012
No, just kids playing.
- They were very eager.

678
00:51:09,340 --> 00:51:12,093
Well then, I'll go to write
that article.

679
00:51:12,300 --> 00:51:13,938
No. Keep the photo.

680
00:51:14,340 --> 00:51:15,853
Show it to kids as well.

681
00:51:16,860 --> 00:51:18,339
Goodbye. 
- Goodbye.

682
00:51:20,500 --> 00:51:23,412
Stig somehow got hold of
Feliks Truu's letters

683
00:51:23,660 --> 00:51:26,220
and Stig hired robbers
to rob your clocks

684
00:51:26,420 --> 00:51:27,694
to get the treasure.

685
00:51:28,020 --> 00:51:31,410
That you have Feliks Truu's clocks,
he found out from the newspaper.

686
00:51:32,220 --> 00:51:35,417
Truu's widow took many of his books
to the second-hand bookstore.

687
00:51:36,300 --> 00:51:38,495
Stig probably bought

688
00:51:39,020 --> 00:51:40,976
"Guide to Photography" from there.

689
00:51:41,260 --> 00:51:45,890
Luckily your clocks are here.
- And treasure is inside one of them.

690
00:51:46,220 --> 00:51:48,734
Mr. Krookus, we need to take
a look at your clocks.

691
00:51:59,980 --> 00:52:00,969
Empty.

692
00:52:02,580 --> 00:52:03,854
That was the last clock.

693
00:52:04,100 --> 00:52:09,049
Maybe there's some somewhere else?
- I bought from Feliks Truu's daughter

694
00:52:10,660 --> 00:52:13,891
five clocks. I remember that.

695
00:52:18,460 --> 00:52:21,372
But I didn't buy all the clocks
from her.

696
00:52:23,540 --> 00:52:26,338
Maybe she has some left.
- What is it?

697
00:52:27,900 --> 00:52:29,652
Probably heard a cat.

698
00:52:33,780 --> 00:52:36,214
This is what we'll do now.

699
00:52:44,020 --> 00:52:45,419
How you're doing, Margit!

700
00:52:45,660 --> 00:52:49,175
Oh, Herman, how nice to see you!

701
00:52:49,380 --> 00:52:50,574
Likewise.

702
00:52:50,780 --> 00:52:52,418
Come on in!

703
00:52:53,500 --> 00:52:56,253
It's been ages since you came by.

704
00:52:56,460 --> 00:52:58,291
Excuse us but we're in a hurry.

705
00:52:58,580 --> 00:53:00,298
Is your husband home?

706
00:53:01,060 --> 00:53:05,099
He's been living in Tallinn for years,
we divorced four years ago.

707
00:53:05,740 --> 00:53:06,650
Oh, how sad.

708
00:53:07,780 --> 00:53:08,929
Let me introduce you,

709
00:53:09,860 --> 00:53:13,330
These are my young friends,
talented young detectives.

710
00:53:13,540 --> 00:53:14,973
Detectives you say!?

711
00:53:15,460 --> 00:53:18,338
Hello, detectives. 
- Hello.

712
00:53:18,780 --> 00:53:21,453
Actually, we came
because of a clock.

713
00:53:21,700 --> 00:53:26,012
That's funny, you're already a
second person today asking this.

714
00:53:26,420 --> 00:53:29,173
10 minutes ago there was one buyer.

715
00:53:30,140 --> 00:53:32,290
Please tell me you didn't
sell this clock?

716
00:53:32,620 --> 00:53:35,692
Yes I did. He offered
such a good price.

717
00:53:36,060 --> 00:53:37,937
And it was a complete wreck.

718
00:53:38,260 --> 00:53:41,332
I really needed the money
to fix this place.

719
00:53:43,860 --> 00:53:46,169
What did this buyer look like?

720
00:53:46,420 --> 00:53:48,456
He was a nice and kind man,

721
00:53:48,660 --> 00:53:52,016
distinguished, about 40,

722
00:53:52,260 --> 00:53:55,058
dark hair, a real gentleman.

723
00:53:55,260 --> 00:53:57,569
Men like that come by very seldom.

724
00:53:57,780 --> 00:54:00,931
It had to be Stig. But how
did he know to come here?

725
00:54:01,260 --> 00:54:05,538
Maybe he listened to us? Remember,
Nassu started barking.

726
00:54:05,860 --> 00:54:08,897
Let's find Stig and see if he found
anything from the clock.

727
00:54:16,740 --> 00:54:21,018
Take your daughter,
you sinner.

728
00:54:21,980 --> 00:54:25,416
Looks like a healthy child.

729
00:54:27,260 --> 00:54:28,056
Johanna

730
00:54:30,380 --> 00:54:31,574
we have a daughter.

731
00:54:35,580 --> 00:54:39,698
But now you have to run
before Bishop finds out.

732
00:54:42,820 --> 00:54:44,697
Bishop and his soldiers.

733
00:54:45,460 --> 00:54:47,212
Save my child.

734
00:54:47,460 --> 00:54:52,488
I cannot save you but maybe
your child.

735
00:55:02,340 --> 00:55:06,333
I heard terrible things,
Brother Bonifacius.

736
00:55:07,900 --> 00:55:09,253
Yes, everything is correct.

737
00:55:09,700 --> 00:55:13,409
Here these sinners are,
I heard about it just now.

738
00:55:16,220 --> 00:55:20,498
A face too flawless,
eyes too beautiful.

739
00:55:23,420 --> 00:55:27,049
I had to be a fool not noticing
this snake.

740
00:55:28,100 --> 00:55:29,055
Where is the child?

741
00:55:30,020 --> 00:55:32,375
Which child? 
- Don't be a fool.

742
00:55:32,580 --> 00:55:35,299
Bonifacius, where is sinful fruit?

743
00:55:35,660 --> 00:55:37,890
My eyes have seen no child.

744
00:55:38,340 --> 00:55:40,979
I swear on Almighty, there was
a child in this room

745
00:55:42,500 --> 00:55:45,060
Brother Gregorius
means Homunculus.

746
00:55:45,380 --> 00:55:49,851
Look, Father, we managed to
complete the Homunculus.

747
00:55:50,060 --> 00:55:51,379
Right now it's in early stages.

748
00:55:51,660 --> 00:55:55,096
We'll deal with the Homunculus later.

749
00:55:55,540 --> 00:55:59,613
Take the sinners
straight away to jail.

750
00:56:09,620 --> 00:56:12,976
What am I going to do
with you, little one?

751
00:56:28,300 --> 00:56:32,179
Now Stig gets the treasure and Feliks
Truu's daughter will lose everything.

752
00:56:47,580 --> 00:56:49,571
So? 
- There was no treasure inside the clock.

753
00:56:50,460 --> 00:56:52,098
Where's the right clock then?

754
00:56:52,700 --> 00:56:56,056
Maybe Mrs. Truu has sold clocks
to someone else as well?

755
00:57:00,300 --> 00:57:02,609
Hello. It's us again.

756
00:57:02,860 --> 00:57:07,092
How nice, come in. 
- Sorry, but we're in a hurry.

757
00:57:07,580 --> 00:57:10,890
Say, you didn't sell anyone else
any of your father's clocks?

758
00:57:11,700 --> 00:57:16,012
Yes, a long time ago I sold another one. 
- To whom?

759
00:57:16,300 --> 00:57:19,895
One big round clock was bought
by Haapsalu's railway museum.

760
00:57:20,140 --> 00:57:23,610
I know that clock.
It's in the station's main hall.

761
00:57:24,620 --> 00:57:27,453
Thank you, Margit. 
- What is it with these clocks?

762
00:57:27,700 --> 00:57:31,409
Can't tell you now. Soon
you'll find out everything.

763
00:57:40,980 --> 00:57:42,493
Don't ask me where did I get her.

764
00:57:42,700 --> 00:57:44,895
Please raise her for a few months

765
00:57:45,100 --> 00:57:47,534
