767
00:58:12,860 --> 00:58:14,498
I don't know, let's ask the guard.

768
00:58:15,620 --> 00:58:18,009
Nobody will allow us
to take down that clock.

769
00:58:18,540 --> 00:58:20,212
But at night there's nobody here.

770
00:58:20,580 --> 00:58:23,936
Let's hide under the benches
and when the doors close,

771
00:58:24,140 --> 00:58:26,495
We'll take the clock down and see
if there's a treasure inside.

772
00:58:26,700 --> 00:58:28,452
I don't know if it's the best idea?

773
00:58:28,660 --> 00:58:33,176
But Feliks Truu's daughter is so poor
and her house needs fixing up.

774
00:58:34,700 --> 00:58:35,769
Yes, that's true.

775
00:58:36,740 --> 00:58:37,968
All right.

776
00:58:38,780 --> 00:58:40,179
Let's do this.

777
00:58:44,100 --> 00:58:44,816
Wait, wait.

778
00:58:45,300 --> 00:58:46,574
Where are you going?

779
00:58:47,580 --> 00:58:50,253
Herman promised to
teach us astronomy.

780
00:58:50,540 --> 00:58:53,179
He'll show us Moon's craters
through his telescope.

781
00:58:53,380 --> 00:58:56,292
Tonight is full moon. 
- And it's supposed to be clear sky.

782
00:58:56,700 --> 00:58:58,930
I'm afraid you'll wear
uncle Herman out.

783
00:58:59,380 --> 00:59:01,450
Mom, uncle Herman is our friend.

784
00:59:01,700 --> 00:59:04,373
And he's really happy
when we visit him

785
00:59:04,660 --> 00:59:06,457
because he himself invited us.

786
00:59:06,700 --> 00:59:08,179
Tonis, what do you think?

787
00:59:08,780 --> 00:59:11,169
Let them go, kids'll have fun.

788
00:59:12,220 --> 00:59:14,290
Okay, but take your phones.

789
00:59:15,380 --> 00:59:17,371
I'll call Herman and check.

790
00:59:20,620 --> 00:59:22,451
Why do you worry for them so much?

791
00:59:22,900 --> 00:59:23,855
Bon appetit!

792
00:59:53,980 --> 00:59:55,095
By what right?

793
00:59:56,860 --> 00:59:57,690
Okay.

794
01:00:09,140 --> 01:00:11,335
That was Stig, I know.
- You bet!

795
01:00:11,540 --> 01:00:14,373
He probably found out from Margit
where another clock was.

796
01:00:14,580 --> 01:00:15,695
Where did he get the key from?

797
01:00:15,900 --> 01:00:18,050
Maybe stole from the guard?
- Or made a copy?

798
01:00:18,300 --> 01:00:19,858
Let's call dad! 
- No!

799
01:00:20,260 --> 01:00:22,933
Then he'll know that we lied.
- Kids!

800
01:00:23,580 --> 01:00:26,777
The situation is bad,
but not hopeless.

801
01:00:27,540 --> 01:00:29,053
He locked us up.

802
01:00:30,100 --> 01:00:32,170
We have to stay here
until morning.

803
01:00:32,900 --> 01:00:34,618
Then we'll see.

804
01:01:18,780 --> 01:01:21,294
Stig has gotten the treasure
from the clock anyway.

805
01:01:21,700 --> 01:01:24,373
I'd like to know what treasure
it was in the clock.

806
01:01:24,580 --> 01:01:25,695
Maybe diamonds.

807
01:01:25,860 --> 01:01:28,852
I don't think that Feliks Truu
would have had diamonds.

808
01:01:29,460 --> 01:01:31,098
They were so poor.

809
01:01:31,420 --> 01:01:34,014
What would have been the point
to hide the treasure?

810
01:01:39,020 --> 01:01:40,772
I'm listening. 
- Hello, Herman.

811
01:01:41,660 --> 01:01:43,776
I'm calling because of my father's clock.

812
01:01:44,300 --> 01:01:46,416
I remembered that Dad
had one more clock.

813
01:01:46,820 --> 01:01:47,809
What?

814
01:01:48,620 --> 01:01:50,656
One more clock? 
- Yes.

815
01:01:50,860 --> 01:01:54,455
I'm right coming over,
with young detectives...

816
01:01:54,700 --> 01:01:55,769
And Margit,

817
01:01:56,460 --> 01:01:59,691
please don't tell anyone
about this clock.

818
01:02:06,780 --> 01:02:10,216
Good morning, Margit!
- Hello Herman, hi kids!

819
01:02:10,420 --> 01:02:12,456
Please, come on in.

820
01:02:13,300 --> 01:02:14,255
Kids,

821
01:02:14,820 --> 01:02:16,094
take your shoes off.

822
01:02:18,540 --> 01:02:19,893
I kept it in the shed.

823
01:02:20,340 --> 01:02:23,173
Dad wouldn't allow me
to throw it out.

824
01:02:23,660 --> 01:02:26,413
Margit, now's the time to
tell you everything -Yes?

825
01:02:26,820 --> 01:02:28,617
We're looking for a valuable treasure.

826
01:02:28,780 --> 01:02:30,816
A treasure hidden in one of your clocks.

827
01:02:31,020 --> 01:02:33,739
In my clock? Who hid it there?

828
01:02:34,260 --> 01:02:36,455
With your permission we'd like
to open the clock now.

829
01:02:36,740 --> 01:02:38,617
Of course. 
- Boys!

830
01:02:47,740 --> 01:02:49,458
Look! 
- Treasure!

831
01:02:57,220 --> 01:03:00,098
It's written by the hand
of monk Bonifacius.

832
01:03:01,220 --> 01:03:02,448
Unbelievable!

833
01:03:03,140 --> 01:03:06,337
It's worth much more
than gold or diamonds.

834
01:03:10,980 --> 01:03:12,299
This is for you.

835
01:03:14,420 --> 01:03:16,490
"My dear daughter,

836
01:03:17,500 --> 01:03:22,574
story of the White Lady
I told you is all true...

837
01:03:23,060 --> 01:03:26,735
During the archaeological dig
I managed to uncover

838
01:03:27,220 --> 01:03:29,939
The diary of monk-alchemist
Bonifacius.

839
01:03:30,580 --> 01:03:32,935
There he describes what happened

840
01:03:33,260 --> 01:03:40,610
in the Bishop's castle of Haapsalu
between 1472 and 1474.

841
01:03:41,220 --> 01:03:44,974
Based on this I wrote the
"True story of the White Lady".

842
01:03:46,620 --> 01:03:50,374
Turns out my Dad's book
was based on reality.

843
01:03:50,820 --> 01:03:51,889
Turns out.

844
01:03:52,260 --> 01:03:54,455
"Alchemist Bonifacius

845
01:03:54,740 --> 01:03:58,369
hid in the Bishop's castle
the instructions for making gold.

846
01:03:59,900 --> 01:04:04,018
He created an intricate light effect
that shows once a year

847
01:04:04,540 --> 01:04:07,532
with full moon the place
where it is hidden...

848
01:04:08,820 --> 01:04:12,449
Unfortunately my healt
is too weak to look for it

849
01:04:12,660 --> 01:04:14,776
and the season is not right.

850
01:04:15,380 --> 01:04:18,019
If you can, please look
for those instructions.

851
01:04:18,540 --> 01:04:20,417
Your loving dad."

852
01:04:22,980 --> 01:04:25,540
Stig! 
- Margit!

853
01:04:26,620 --> 01:04:29,054
Don't tell him that we're here.

854
01:04:29,780 --> 01:04:31,418
That is a very dangerous man.

855
01:04:31,660 --> 01:04:33,890
He wants to get your father's treasure.

856
01:04:34,740 --> 01:04:35,650
Hello!

857
01:04:37,620 --> 01:04:39,451
Me again, because of those clocks.

858
01:04:39,660 --> 01:04:40,854
Hello-hello.

859
01:04:41,060 --> 01:04:43,972
Maybe that's the treasure map? 
- No.

860
01:04:44,820 --> 01:04:47,209
That's Bishop's castle's blueprint.

861
01:04:47,540 --> 01:04:50,577
See. That's the christening chapel.

862
01:04:51,860 --> 01:04:52,815
Right.

863
01:04:53,100 --> 01:04:56,012
Tell me, did your father leave you
any more clocks?

864
01:04:56,260 --> 01:04:58,376
All that I had I sold.

865
01:04:58,700 --> 01:04:59,815
That's a pity.

866
01:05:06,260 --> 01:05:12,495
Here is written in Latin:
"Look for it in August, at full moon."

867
01:05:16,460 --> 01:05:21,659
White Lady will show you the way.

868
01:05:23,220 --> 01:05:26,337
Oh, well, have a great day, Missis.
- Have a nice day.

869
01:05:31,220 --> 01:05:35,008
We have to find that treasure.
- That's exactly what we'll do.

870
01:05:37,700 --> 01:05:42,455
Let's meet a little before midnight
at the museum's front door.

871
01:05:44,260 --> 01:05:46,171
How do we get in there?

872
01:05:46,340 --> 01:05:49,377
My mom has the museum's keys
and I have a copy.

873
01:05:49,820 --> 01:05:54,098
Sorry to interrupt, I'm so glad
that you want to help me,

874
01:05:54,340 --> 01:05:56,900
but isn't this too dangerous?
- Margit, don't worry.

875
01:05:58,220 --> 01:06:01,371
We're used to danger. Right, kids?

876
01:06:01,660 --> 01:06:02,809
Of course.

877
01:06:03,100 --> 01:06:06,172
I'm sure that Johanna and Jacob
managed to make gold

878
01:06:06,620 --> 01:06:09,373
and that it is buried somewhere
in the chapel...

879
01:06:09,700 --> 01:06:11,611
If only it was already midnight.

880
01:06:16,740 --> 01:06:18,890
Maid Johanna.

881
01:06:20,420 --> 01:06:24,254
You have violated
our sacred rules that state

882
01:06:24,660 --> 01:06:30,257
that no woman shall ever
set foot inside the castle.

883
01:06:32,060 --> 01:06:35,177
Therefore we are sentencing you

884
01:06:35,620 --> 01:06:38,498
in the name of the divine power.

885
01:06:38,980 --> 01:06:43,178
What is the punishment for the sinner?

886
01:06:43,660 --> 01:06:45,173
Death.

887
01:06:48,820 --> 01:06:51,698
The same goes for you, Jacob

888
01:06:52,980 --> 01:06:57,292
You have sinned and
concealed this from us.

889
01:06:58,540 --> 01:07:01,612
What shall be his punishment?

890
01:07:02,980 --> 01:07:04,732
Death.

891
01:07:07,780 --> 01:07:09,657
Hereby we sentence,

892
01:07:11,380 --> 01:07:12,893
that Johanna

893
01:07:13,780 --> 01:07:15,691
shall be walled up alive

894
01:07:17,580 --> 01:07:19,935
into the wall of the christening chapel.

895
01:07:22,220 --> 01:07:29,774
Monk Jacob shall be executed.
Sentence will be carried out immediately.

896
01:07:42,540 --> 01:07:46,453
Hello. Your name must be?
- Yes, hello.

897
01:07:47,300 --> 01:07:48,972
I need to talk to your mother.

898
01:07:49,660 --> 01:07:50,979
Kids, go play.

899
01:07:53,780 --> 01:07:55,691
Sorry, didn't mean to interrupt.

900
01:07:55,900 --> 01:07:58,778
What are you talking about,
you're not interrupting.

901
01:07:59,020 --> 01:08:00,499
Hello. 
- Hello.

902
01:08:01,420 --> 01:08:03,729
I see that you have read
my article.

903
01:08:04,060 --> 01:08:06,494
Yes, I did and it was
simply amazing...

904
01:08:06,860 --> 01:08:08,213
One agency wishes

905
01:08:08,420 --> 01:08:10,809
That I would take White Lady's photo
tonight, at the same place.

906
01:08:11,260 --> 01:08:15,412
I'm sure that tonight, with
full moon, she will reappear.

907
01:08:16,460 --> 01:08:19,657
Tell me, Berit, could you come
to the castle with me tonight?

908
01:08:19,900 --> 01:08:23,609
Of course, no problem. You made
our castle world famous.

909
01:08:23,860 --> 01:08:25,816
I'm sure it'll be crowded tonight.

910
01:08:26,300 --> 01:08:29,053
If you don't mind I'd like to join you.
I have an evening off.

911
01:08:30,740 --> 01:08:31,695
Fabulous.

912
01:08:32,420 --> 01:08:33,739
See you at midnight.

913
01:08:34,540 --> 01:08:36,178
Goodbye. 
- Goodbye.

914
01:08:36,860 --> 01:08:38,088
Yes, this is Piir.

915
01:08:39,660 --> 01:08:41,890
Okay. I'll drive there straight away.

916
01:08:42,260 --> 01:08:45,297
Don't tell me that you can't come
to see White Lady with us.

917
01:08:45,500 --> 01:08:48,856
I've been called to Dirham.
- I just had to marry a policeman.

918
01:08:49,100 --> 01:08:51,091
There's nothing you can do about it now.

919
01:08:51,300 --> 01:08:54,770
I think you won't be bored with
those ghouls and ghostbusters, right?

920
01:08:55,460 --> 01:08:57,178
I'll come to pick you up afterwards.

921
01:09:02,460 --> 01:09:03,939
You're not even ready yet?

922
01:09:04,540 --> 01:09:08,010
We don't want to see the White Lady.
- We've seen her every year.

923
01:09:08,340 --> 01:09:12,219
You've always waited for this anxiously.
Rosanna and Karl?

924
01:09:12,420 --> 01:09:14,411
We'll go to bed earlier today.

925
01:09:14,620 --> 01:09:17,088
Yes. And we're very tired.

926
01:09:18,300 --> 01:09:21,292
As you wish. I'm surprised.

927
01:09:47,220 --> 01:09:49,734
No! No! No!

928
01:09:58,540 --> 01:10:01,054
You won't get in trouble with your mom?

929
01:10:02,100 --> 01:10:05,649
White Lady's treasure
is more important. 
- Agreed.

930
01:10:36,260 --> 01:10:40,572
Dear child, I brought you
something to eat and drink.

931
01:10:46,100 --> 01:10:50,173
But I can't help you out as
there are guards everywhere.

932
01:10:51,820 --> 01:10:53,253
How is Jacob?

933
01:10:53,940 --> 01:10:55,339
He was executed.

934
01:10:56,260 --> 01:10:57,375
But my child?

935
01:10:57,700 --> 01:11:00,772
She's fine. She's at my sister's.

936
01:11:03,820 --> 01:11:07,017
I can no longer come,
but I promise you this,

937
01:11:07,260 --> 01:11:10,650
That I'll take care of your little girl
as if she was my own flesh and blood.

938
01:11:12,340 --> 01:11:14,979
Here is the cure.

939
01:11:16,260 --> 01:11:18,410
It will grant you sleep,
without any pain.

940
01:11:19,900 --> 01:11:20,969
Johanna.

941
01:11:22,100 --> 01:11:25,729
What should I do with your instructions
for making gold?

942
01:11:26,020 --> 01:11:27,817
Minul seda enam vaja ei lahe.

943
01:11:28,260 --> 01:11:32,048
Koige rohkem kahetsen ma seda,
et ma oma eliksiiri katsetada ei saanud.

944
01:11:32,620 --> 01:11:34,417
I'll hide it in such a place,

945
01:11:34,660 --> 01:11:36,059
your instructions,

946
01:11:36,580 --> 01:11:39,777
where nobody will be able
to find it for some time.

947
01:11:40,620 --> 01:11:42,929
And you shall show them
the way,

948
01:11:43,460 --> 01:11:45,928
where this priceless treasure lies...

949
01:11:46,780 --> 01:11:47,769
Goodbye.

950
01:11:48,620 --> 01:11:49,848
Go with God, Johanna.

951
01:12:00,900 --> 01:12:04,051
Berit, I have a huge request.

952
01:12:04,380 --> 01:12:07,452
Would it be possible to take
a few shots inside the castle?

953
01:12:08,420 --> 01:12:11,730
No. At nights we don't let
the visitors in.

954
01:12:14,380 --> 01:12:18,009
But since you've done such
a great job promoting our castle,

955
01:12:18,260 --> 01:12:19,978
Then I'll have to make an exception.

956
01:12:20,220 --> 01:12:21,733
Come this way.

957
01:12:55,140 --> 01:12:57,734
White Lady should appear
within 15 minutes.

958
01:12:59,900 --> 01:13:01,458
Hide, quickly!

959
01:13:04,380 --> 01:13:07,736
This is the christening chapel

960
01:13:07,940 --> 01:13:10,295
And that's the window where
White Lady will appear on.

961
01:13:11,540 --> 01:13:12,734
That's an optical trick.

962
01:13:13,460 --> 01:13:16,418
I'm more interested in the basement
where she was walled in.

963
01:13:17,100 --> 01:13:18,249
Do you have the key?

964
01:13:18,460 --> 01:13:21,770
Of course. Come with me.

965
01:13:28,820 --> 01:13:29,650
Lucky.

966
01:13:29,980 --> 01:13:34,258
Let them go and look in the basement,
then they won't disturb us.

967
01:13:50,540 --> 01:13:53,418
If Bonifacius is right,

968
01:13:54,060 --> 01:13:56,938
then something is about to start.

969
01:14:00,620 --> 01:14:01,655
See!

970
01:14:10,700 --> 01:14:12,292
The White Lady

971
01:14:15,140 --> 01:14:17,973
points at this stone here.

972
01:14:23,580 --> 01:14:25,650
Help me to lift it.

973
01:14:54,380 --> 01:14:55,495
Hold this.

974
01:15:01,220 --> 01:15:04,735
That's Johanna's instruction
for making gold

975
01:15:10,700 --> 01:15:13,658
and recipe for the curing elixir.

976
01:15:14,500 --> 01:15:15,979
And gold.

977
01:15:16,700 --> 01:15:18,497
And lots of it.

978
01:15:18,780 --> 01:15:21,817
Margit Truu has now enough
money to fix her home.

979
01:15:25,620 --> 01:15:26,894
I'm afraid not.

980
01:15:39,100 --> 01:15:40,294
Children!

981
01:15:42,220 --> 01:15:45,610
Nassu, where are you running, wait.

982
01:15:46,940 --> 01:15:49,170
Wait, where are you going now?

983
01:15:49,820 --> 01:15:52,254
Where do you want to go? Wait!

984
01:15:55,500 --> 01:15:57,855
Faster. Go, go.

985
01:16:00,260 --> 01:16:03,536
Those are my Mom's keys.
- Sharp eye, detective.

986
01:16:05,740 --> 01:16:09,528
You know, Stig? Locking me
down here isn't funny. 
- Silence!

987
01:16:09,820 --> 01:16:11,538
Inside! Quickly!

988
01:16:12,500 --> 01:16:14,331
Kids, what are you doing here?

989
01:16:16,220 --> 01:16:19,098
That man's a robber, Mom.
- Harsh words, young man...

990
01:16:19,420 --> 01:16:21,775
I don't understand anything anymore!

991
01:16:22,060 --> 01:16:24,290
You'll have plenty of time
to catch up.

992
01:16:24,900 --> 01:16:28,939
Mom, Stig is getting away with the
treasure, you have to do something!

993
01:16:29,140 --> 01:16:31,973
Let him go, main thing is
that you're alive

994
01:16:32,580 --> 01:16:34,889
You don't understand anything!

995
01:16:35,260 --> 01:16:38,377
We found Johanna's instructions
for making gold

996
01:16:38,580 --> 01:16:42,289
and a little gold and now
you're just letting him go.

997
01:16:42,500 --> 01:16:46,209
We have to get out of here right now

998
01:16:46,620 --> 01:16:49,339
And we have to catch
this no good robber.

999
01:16:50,740 --> 01:16:52,970
Markus, where did you get these?

1000
01:16:53,300 --> 01:16:54,972
Later, Mom.

1001
01:16:55,260 --> 01:16:57,569
Okay, open this door very quietly.

1002
01:17:11,820 --> 01:17:14,050
What's this supposed to mean?
- Wait-wait.

1003
01:17:14,980 --> 01:17:17,653
It means that you're going
through that door.

1004
01:17:17,860 --> 01:17:20,328
If you're lucky, you'll meet
your family.

1005
01:18:10,380 --> 01:18:13,736
Me, monk-alchemist Bonifacius

1006
01:18:14,300 --> 01:18:18,339
Wrote this down in the year
of our Lord 1481.

1007
01:18:20,340 --> 01:18:23,889
Since I don't want the manuscript
to fall into wrong hands

1008
01:18:24,100 --> 01:18:28,332
I shall hide it into the floor
of the Bishop's castle.

1009
01:18:28,940 --> 01:18:31,693
I hope that some day it will
end up in good hands.

1010
01:18:42,980 --> 01:18:45,335
Praise the Lord!

1011
01:18:48,100 --> 01:18:51,854
Mom, we found Johanna's
instructions for making gold.

1012
01:18:52,140 --> 01:18:53,255
And a little bit of gold.

1013
01:18:53,580 --> 01:18:56,970
She did numerous curing elixirs,
you could get better with these.

1014
01:18:57,580 --> 01:18:59,935
Dear kids, I'm really grateful,

1015
01:19:00,140 --> 01:19:02,938
But it seems I'm already getting better.

1016
01:19:03,340 --> 01:19:06,377
Doctor told me this morning that
the tests have improved vastly.

1017
01:19:06,580 --> 01:19:07,535
Finally!

1018
